Explanation: When a document is notarized, it means that a notary public has verified the identity of the person signing the document and has witnessed the signing. Therefore, if a document "might be notarized," it implies that there is a possibility that it will go through the notarization process. This does not necessarily mean that the document will definitely be signed before being notarized. It is possible for a document to be notarized without being signed first.
